Food Order App - Two-Tier Secure Architecture

Production-Ready Multi-Tier Web Application on AWS

Engineered a secure two-tier architecture implementing defense-in-depth principles with complete network isolation between public and private resources. Features a Flask-based proxy layer, private backend API, and RDS MySQL database with automated provisioning and CORS-enabled client access.

Key Achievements

  • Architected public/private subnet topology with strict security group policies for multi-layer isolation
  • Deployed Flask proxy on public EC2 to route authenticated requests to private backend infrastructure
  • Configured RDS MySQL in private subnet with restricted access only from internal application servers
  • Implemented CORS policies and request validation for secure browser-based interactions
  • Automated database schema creation and connection pooling for high-availability operations
  • Established least-privilege IAM roles and security group rules following AWS best practices

Secure Three-Tier AWS Architecture

Enterprise-Grade Scalable Infrastructure Deployment

Designed and deployed production-ready three-tier architecture with high availability across multiple availability zones. Implemented Application Load Balancer with Auto Scaling for fault tolerance, private subnet database isolation, and automated infrastructure provisioning via GitHub integration.

Technical Implementation

  • Engineered VPC with public/private subnet architecture, custom route tables, and Network ACLs for defense-in-depth security
  • Configured Application Load Balancer with health checks and Auto Scaling groups for 99.9% uptime SLA
  • Deployed backend API servers in private subnets accessible only through internal load balancer endpoints
  • Isolated RDS MySQL database in private subnet with least-privilege security group rules and IAM policies
  • Implemented EC2 User Data scripts for automated application deployment from GitHub repositories
  • Configured multi-AZ deployment strategy for high availability and disaster recovery capabilities

Serverless Portfolio with Real-Time Analytics

Cloud-Native Application with Global CDN Distribution

Built a fully serverless static website with global content delivery, real-time visitor tracking, and atomic database operations. Leveraged AWS managed services for zero infrastructure management, automatic scaling, and pay-per-use cost optimization.

Serverless Architecture Highlights

  • Deployed static website on S3 with CloudFront CDN for sub-100ms global latency and HTTPS encryption
  • Developed Lambda function with atomic DynamoDB increments for accurate concurrent visitor counting
  • Exposed serverless backend via API Gateway with CORS policies, request throttling, and IAM authorization
  • Implemented S3 versioning and CloudFront cache invalidation for zero-downtime deployments
  • Achieved 99.99% availability with fully managed services and automatic fault tolerance
  • Optimized costs with Lambda's pay-per-request model and DynamoDB's on-demand billing
